{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480808","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480808"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:51:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:51:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"112"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"112","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/112"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.19,0.04,0.51,0.21]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"112"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77112"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"112","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/112"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"112"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62618"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"2947"},{"type":"tags","id":"2977"},{"type":"tags","id":"3505"},{"type":"tags","id":"3871"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4963"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11636"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1623"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1695"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41992"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43958"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77112","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77112"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic for review of his type 2 diabetes mellitus care plan. He has a medical history of hypertension, hypercholesterolaemia and gallstones. His medications include atorvastatin, ramipril, and metformin. He works as an accountant.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 90/min, blood pressure 180/100 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. His BMI is 31 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. Fundoscopy reveals copper wiring of retinal arterioles and cotton wool spots. A random capillary blood glucose is 9.2 mmol/L (4.0-7.8).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management of the retinal findings?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Argon laser photocoagulation","Anti-vascular endothelial growth factor injections","Lifestyle modification with review in three months","Urgent antihypertensive therapy","Intensive glucose control"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with hypertensive retinopathy, evidenced by copper wiring (arteriolar thickening) and cotton wool spots (retinal microinfarcts), along with significantly elevated blood pressure. \u003Cstrong\u003EUrgent antihypertensive therapy\u003C/strong\u003E is essential to prevent further end-organ damage and is the most appropriate next step in management.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArgon laser photocoagulation\u003C/strong\u003E is used in proliferative diabetic retinopathy and has no role in the management of hypertensive retinopathy. While this patient has diabetes, the retinal findings are more consistent with hypertensive damage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnti-vascular endothelial growth factor injections\u003C/strong\u003E are primarily used for conditions like wet age-related macular degeneration or diabetic macular oedema. They do not address the underlying pathology of hypertensive retinopathy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELifestyle modification\u003C/strong\u003E alone with delayed review would be inappropriate given the presence of end-organ damage. The elevated blood pressure requires more urgent intervention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntensive glucose control\u003C/strong\u003E, while important for this patient\u0027s overall health, is not the immediate priority. His random glucose is only mildly elevated, and the retinal changes are more consistent with hypertensive rather than diabetic retinopathy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHypertensive retinopathy represents end-organ damage and, combined with a blood pressure of 180/100 mmHg, constitutes a hypertensive urgency requiring prompt medical attention. The goal is to prevent progression to malignant hypertension and further end-organ damage.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hypertensive retinopathy with copper wiring and cotton wool spots requires urgent blood pressure control to prevent further end-organ damage.","Copper wiring represents arteriolar thickening from chronic hypertension, while cotton wool spots indicate acute retinal microinfarction.","Blood pressure of 180/100 mmHg with end-organ damage constitutes a hypertensive urgency requiring prompt intervention."],"references":["Harjasouliha A, Raiji V, Gonzalez JMG. Review of hypertensive retinopathy\u00a0 Dis Mon 2017; 63:63-69. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27931746/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62618"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"112"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62618","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62618"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-06T09:23:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-06T09:23:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"i